el","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Aime, Alcide, Yves, Aurel, Aurele, Euclide, Jacques, Josee, Marcel.","French: topographic name derived from Norman, Picard <i>quesne</i> ‘oak tree’, or a habitational name from (Le) Quesnel, the name of several places in the north of France, named from the same word. Compare   Canell   and   Quesnell  .","History: Olivier Quesnel from Bayeux in Calvados, France, married Catherine Prudhomme (Louis and Roberte Gadois) in Montreal, QC, in 1680."]}]},{"name":"Henry","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705205,"age":8,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705206,"age":10,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705207,"age":24,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705208,"age":26,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705210,"age":39,"year":"1600","julianDay":2305448,"title":"The Honourable East India Company","description":"The Honourable East India Company, a British joint-stock company, was established in 1600 for trade in the Indian Ocean region. At its height, the British East India Company had a private army which was twice the size of the British Army, ruled large sections of India, and revenues in the millions.","url":"https://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/HistoryofEngland/The-East-India-Company/","urlTitle":"Historic UK - The East India Company","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Henry Quenell III was born on 16 September 1560, in Horsham, Sussex, England, his father, Mr. Quenell, was 37 and his mother, Mrs. Quenell, was 33. He married Beatrix Carter on 30 January 1586, in Horsham, Sussex, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died before 18 May 1615, in his hometown, and was buried in Horsham, Sussex, England."},"et":{"16 September 1560–before 18 May 1615":"16. september 1560–enne 18. maid 1615","1560–1615":"1560–1615","1565–1610":"1565–1610","1587–1628":"1587–1628","1523–Male":"1523–Surnud","1527–Female":"1527–Surnud","before 18 May 1615":"enne 18. maid 1615","1571":"1571","1560":"1560","18 May 1615":"18. mai 1615","30 January 1585/86":"30. jaanuar 1586","1569":"1569","17 April 1587":"17. aprill 1587","1600":"1600","1523":"1523","1610":"1610","1587":"1587","1565":"1565","before 2 July 1610":"enne 2. juulit 1610","1585":"1585","       1554":"1554","16 September 1560":"16. september 1560","1628":"16